<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-03-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="529" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">No. 529.</seg></opener>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Reed</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-03-23"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 23,
                            1885</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 322.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to instruction No. 312 of the 27th
                        ultimo, I inclose in the case of the Ocean Pearl, fined at Stanzas, a copy
                        of a dispatch from our consul there and also a certificate which he
                        transmitted touching the ten empty hogsheads mentioned in the above
                        instructions.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>T. F. BAYARD.</signed></closer>
                    <frus:attachment>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure 1 in No. 322.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Vickers</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Davis</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">United
                                        States Consulate</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Stanzas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-02-20"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 20,
                                    1885</date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 116.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I herewith inclose certificate of Edward
                            K. Sparks, esq., of the firm of Isaac Hough &amp; Co., of Philadelphia,
                            relating to the shipment of 235 empty molasses hogsheads in place of 245
                            as manifested, the absence of which caused the fine to be imposed on the
                            American barkentine Ocean Pearl.</p>
                        <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                        <closer><signed>DAVID BICKERS,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Consul.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </frus:attachment>
                    <frus:attachment>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure 2 in No. 322.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Affidavit of Edward K. Sparks</hi>.</head>
                        <p>Personally appeared before me Edward K. Sparks, of the firm of Isaac
                            Hough &amp;, Co., shipping and commission merchants doing business in
                            Philadelphia, who deposes and says that his firm shipped on the Ocean
                            Pearl, bound for Stanzas, on or about December 7, 1884, 235 empty
                            molasses hogsheads, not 245 as manifested, 10 of them having been left
                            on the wharf.</p>
                        <closer><signed>EDM. K. SPARKS.</signed>
                            <lb/>
                            <dateline rendition="#left"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-02-13">this 13th day of
                                    February, 1885</date>.</dateline></closer>
                        <closer>
                            <dateline rendition="#left">Sworn and subscribed before me <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-02-13">this 13th day of
                                    February, 1885</date>.</dateline>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="smallcaps">seal.</hi>]<lb/><signed>THOMAS M.
                                    CRANE,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Notary
                            Public.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </frus:attachment>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>